package build description for anaconda
=========================================

`Anaconda <https://www.continuum.io/why-anaconda>`_ provides an enterprise-ready data analytics platform that empowers companies to adopt a modern open data science analytics architecture. 


We have setup a channel for mss (tbd). For installation you need the conda-forge channel added to your .condarc. 

.condarc
==============

channels:
  - defaults
  - conda-forge


package build
===============
On top level dir 

* conda build .


developers installation
================================

* conda create -n mssenv path/to/mss-1.1b1-py27_1.tar.bz2
* source activate mssenv
* conda install --use-local mss

optional you could also run for uncommited not published changes 
python setup.py install


users installation
===================================

* conda create -n mssenv mss
* source activate mssenv


Usage:
====================
We have to provide a path where mss_settings.py is located.
mss_settings.py can be retrieved from `the sample file <https://bitbucket.org/wxmetvis/mss/raw/b86175bcb8cfb6e104ab7b0be650194c75b6d9da/msui/mss_settings.py.sample>`_ and adopted.

export PYTHONPATH="$HOME/.config/"

* source activate mssenv
* mss 
